{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01V5a4zmnD83r5yzhEwGviGS","type":"tool_result","content":"54-  exactly `Bugs` is the bug-priority section.\n55-- Four operational tags: `[USER]` (`_USER_TAG`, line 22),\n56-  `[BATCH]` (`_BATCH_TAG`, line 23), `[AUTO:<action>]`\n57:  (`_AUTO_TAG_RE`, line 24), and `[RULEDOUT]` as a non-task\n58-  indent-attached line (handled in `parse`, lines 189-204).\n59-- `PlanCorruptionError` (line 27) is raised on duplicate H1 titles,\n60-  multiple `## Bugs` sections, or duplicate phase/stage numbers.\n--\n82-- `[BATCH]` parents collect consecutive unchecked children via\n83-  `get_batch_children` (line 654) and run them as a single\n84-  session. `[USER]` or `[AUTO:…]` children halt batch collection.\n85:- `[RULEDOUT]` lines feed `get_eliminated(tasks, task)` whose result\n86-  is appended to the task prompt as a \"RULED OUT APPROACHES\" block,\n87-  suppressing repeat strategies (verified in\n88-  `mcloop/runner.py`, lines 376-385, 422-431, and 482-491).\n--\n312-- [ ] T-000001: [BATCH] Markdown checklist parser\n313-  - [ ] T-000002: Parse tasks from markdown checkboxes\n314-  - [ ] T-000003: Find the next unchecked item\n315:    [RULEDOUT] Do not identify tasks by text alone; duplicate text is legal.\n316-  - [x] T-000004: Check off completed items in the file\n317-- [ ] T-000005: [USER] Launch the app and confirm the main window appears\n318-- [ ] T-000006: [AUTO:run_cli] mcloop --dry-run\n--\n348-ActionTag   ← \"[AUTO:\" Word \"]\" WS Text?          ; args are remainder of text\n349-Annot       ← WS \"[\" Key \":\" WS Value \"]\"         ; e.g. [feat: \"...\"], [fix: \"...\"]\n350-DepsLine    ← Indent* \"@deps\" (WS TaskRef)+ NL    ; bare IDs, no trailing colon\n351:RuledOut    ← Indent* \"[RULEDOUT]\" WS Text NL\n352-Indent      ← (WS WS)+                            ; numeric nesting, 2-space canonical\n353-Prose       ← (! Item ! PhaseHead ! Subsection . )* NL\n354-```\n--\n403-description mentions `[USER]` in prose leaves the bracket form as\n404-text; it does not silently convert the task into a USER task.\n405-\n406:`[RULEDOUT]` is **not** a task tag. It is a sibling line at the\n407-child indent under the task it pertains to, matching McLoop's\n408-existing convention. Reserved for the indent-attached rule.\n409-\n--\n714-   projects.) `bob-plan fmt` should handle all four. Verify\n715-   round-trip on each before claiming Phase A complete.\n716-\n717:3. **Should `[RULEDOUT]` move from sibling-line to a field on `Task`?**\n718-   The runtime behavior is identical (collected and fed to the\n719-   prompt); the only difference is whether it appears as\n720-   indent-attached prose or as a structured field. The current sibling-\n721-   line form survives canonicalization unchanged; the structured form\n722-   would require a schema decision. Recommendation: keep sibling-line\n723:   form; treat `[RULEDOUT]` as a parser-collected per-task list in the\n724-   `Task` object. No syntax change.\n725-\n726-4. **How are `## Stage` and `## Phase` headings reconciled?** Both"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3c62b045-7b08-4482-8a85-a083b3158292","uuid":"b50081c6-e0fb-4cd0-a6d9-5e6d797d3d62","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:58:40.927Z","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"54-  exactly `Bugs` is the bug-priority section.\n55-- Four operational tags: `[USER]` (`_USER_TAG`, line 22),\n56-  `[BATCH]` (`_BATCH_TAG`, line 23), `[AUTO:<action>]`\n57:  (`_AUTO_TAG_RE`, line 24), and `[RULEDOUT]` as a non-task\n58-  indent-attached line (handled in `parse`, lines 189-204).\n59-- `PlanCorruptionError` (line 27) is raised on duplicate H1 titles,\n60-  multiple `## Bugs` sections, or duplicate phase/stage numbers.\n--\n82-- `[BATCH]` parents collect consecutive unchecked children via\n83-  `get_batch_children` (line 654) and run them as a single\n84-  session. `[USER]` or `[AUTO:…]` children halt batch collection.\n85:- `[RULEDOUT]` lines feed `get_eliminated(tasks, task)` whose result\n86-  is appended to the task prompt as a \"RULED OUT APPROACHES\" block,\n87-  suppressing repeat strategies (verified in\n88-  `mcloop/runner.py`, lines 376-385, 422-431, and 482-491).\n--\n312-- [ ] T-000001: [BATCH] Markdown checklist parser\n313-  - [ ] T-000002: Parse tasks from markdown checkboxes\n314-  - [ ] T-000003: Find the next unchecked item\n315:    [RULEDOUT] Do not identify tasks by text alone; duplicate text is legal.\n316-  - [x] T-000004: Check off completed items in the file\n317-- [ ] T-000005: [USER] Launch the app and confirm the main window appears\n318-- [ ] T-000006: [AUTO:run_cli] mcloop --dry-run\n--\n348-ActionTag   ← \"[AUTO:\" Word \"]\" WS Text?          ; args are remainder of text\n349-Annot       ← WS \"[\" Key \":\" WS Value \"]\"         ; e.g. [feat: \"...\"], [fix: \"...\"]\n350-DepsLine    ← Indent* \"@deps\" (WS TaskRef)+ NL    ; bare IDs, no trailing colon\n351:RuledOut    ← Indent* \"[RULEDOUT]\" WS Text NL\n352-Indent      ← (WS WS)+                            ; numeric nesting, 2-space canonical\n353-Prose       ← (! Item ! PhaseHead ! Subsection . )* NL\n354-```\n--\n403-description mentions `[USER]` in prose leaves the bracket form as\n404-text; it does not silently convert the task into a USER task.\n405-\n406:`[RULEDOUT]` is **not** a task tag. It is a sibling line at the\n407-child indent under the task it pertains to, matching McLoop's\n408-existing convention. Reserved for the indent-attached rule.\n409-\n--\n714-   projects.) `bob-plan fmt` should handle all four. Verify\n715-   round-trip on each before claiming Phase A complete.\n716-\n717:3. **Should `[RULEDOUT]` move from sibling-line to a field on `Task`?**\n718-   The runtime behavior is identical (collected and fed to the\n719-   prompt); the only difference is whether it appears as\n720-   indent-attached prose or as a structured field. The current sibling-\n721-   line form survives canonicalization unch