{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FVuB6vd9Nr3VyoM4Hs7pMx","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Tests for bob_tools.planfile.parser building blocks.\n2\t\n3\tStage 2 task-line recognizers and tag extractors:\n4\t\n5\t  - ``_CHECKBOX_RE`` matches indented/bare checkboxes for every status\n6\t    marker (space, ``x``, ``X``, ``!``); rejects malformed forms.\n7\t  - ``_parse_task_line`` returns a raw record on checkbox lines and\n8\t    ``None`` on anything else.\n9\t  - ``_parse_ruledout_line`` recognizes leading-position ``[RULEDOUT]``\n10\t    sibling lines and returns indent, body, and source line number.\n11\t  - ``_attach_ruledout`` resolves the attachment target for a RULEDOUT\n12\t    line: nearest strictly-less-indented open ancestor, with fallback\n13\t    to the most recent root task (mcloop's ``parse`` parity).\n14\t  - ``_extract_flag_tags`` consumes leading ``[USER]`` / ``[BATCH]``\n15\t    tokens, in isolation and combination, and leaves non-leading\n16\t    occurrences as prose (design doc section 4.3).\n17\t  - ``_extract_action_tag`` consumes a leading ``[AUTO:<action>]`` and\n18\t    treats the rest of the line as its argument string; non-leading\n19\t    occurrences are prose.\n20\t  - ``_extract_annotations`` consumes trailing ``[key: value]``\n21\t    annotations, handles multiple annotations and nested brackets in\n22\t    values, and leaves bracketed prose that is not separated from\n23\t    preceding text by whitespace in place.\n24\t\"\"\"\n25\t\n26\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n27\t\n28\timport pytest\n29\t\n30\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n31\t\n32\tfrom bob_tools.planfile.parser import (\n33\t    _CHECKBOX_RE,\n34\t    _attach_ruledout,\n35\t    _extract_action_tag,\n36\t    _extract_annotations,\n37\t    _extract_flag_tags,\n38\t    _parse_ruledout_line,\n39\t    _parse_task_line,\n40\t)\n41\t\n42\t\n43\t@dataclass\n44\tclass _FakeTask:\n45\t    \"\"\"Minimal indent-bearing stand-in for the attachment-logic tests.\"\"\"\n46\t\n47\t    indent_level: int\n48\t    name: str = \"\"\n49\t\n50\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3c62b045-7b08-4482-8a85-a083b3158292","uuid":"078b7bff-995c-478e-8312-a3dd475316fb","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:59:34.469Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/mhcoen/proj/bob-tools/bob_tools/planfile/tests/test_parser.py","content":"\"\"\"Tests for bob_tools.planfile.parser building blocks.\n\nStage 2 task-line recognizers and tag extractors:\n\n  - ``_CHECKBOX_RE`` matches indented/bare checkboxes for every status\n    marker (space, ``x``, ``X``, ``!``); rejects malformed forms.\n  - ``_parse_task_line`` returns a raw record on checkbox lines and\n    ``None`` on anything else.\n  - ``_parse_ruledout_line`` recognizes leading-position ``[RULEDOUT]``\n    sibling lines and returns indent, body, and source line number.\n  - ``_attach_ruledout`` resolves the attachment target for a RULEDOUT\n    line: nearest strictly-less-indented open ancestor, with fallback\n    to the most recent root task (mcloop's ``parse`` parity).\n  - ``_extract_flag_tags`` consumes leading ``[USER]`` / ``[BATCH]``\n    tokens, in isolation and combination, and leaves non-leading\n    occurrences as prose (design doc section 4.3).\n  - ``_extract_action_tag`` consumes a leading ``[AUTO:<action>]`` and\n    treats the rest of the line as its argument string; non-leading\n    occurrences are prose.\n  - ``_extract_annotations`` consumes trailing ``[key: value]``\n    annotations, handles multiple annotations and nested brackets in\n    values, and leaves bracketed prose that is not separated from\n    preceding text by whitespace in place.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport pytest\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n\nfrom bob_tools.planfile.parser import (\n    _CHECKBOX_RE,\n    _attach_ruledout,\n    _extract_action_tag,\n    _extract_annotations,\n    _extract_flag_tags,\n    _parse_ruledout_line,\n    _parse_task_line,\n)\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass _FakeTask:\n    \"\"\"Minimal indent-bearing stand-in for the attachment-logic tests.\"\"\"\n\n    indent_level: int\n    name: str = \"\"\n\n","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":349}}}
